# Pilots’ Tavern — Illustration Prompt

Create a richly detailed, roughly square digital painting sized to sit beside narrative text on desktop or mobile screens. Depict a grounded late-medieval harbor campaign setting in a pilot-heavy tavern with tide marks, benches, chalk, wet cloaks, mugs, and maritime argument. Emphasize crisp readability, brighter maritime color accents, and clear spatial separation more than muddy painterly atmosphere.

- Composition: harbor tavern interior close to the quay, with a visible exit back toward the berth.
- Key elements: tide slates, local charts, mugs, dripping cloaks, and men arguing over local water knowledge.
- Character focus: pilots loudly certain that the ship is ready apart from one tiny issue of tide interpretation.
- Navigation hint: keep the exit back toward Launch Quay obvious and well-lit.

